evaluation.response:
Sometimes we feel overwhelmed and things can feel like they're falling apart, but with some support and guidance, we can make it through. Let's take this step by step so you can feel better in this situation.&#x20;

Firstly, your feelings are valid. It's okay to feel like this. You're not alone in feeling this way.

Secondsly, while it might feel like your only option right now, ending things isn't the only way out. There are things you can do to feel better about this situation you are in.

Lastly, you don't have to go through this alone. Reaching out to a trusted friend or family member could provide you with the support you need to get through these difficult times.&#x20;

Take a moment to document everything that's happening. These are signs that something more might be going on. Next, consider who you can trust to reach out to for support. Be it a professional, a friend, family member, romantic partner or acquaintance that you think would be able to help you on this journey, having a confidant that you can potentially open up to might be of great value. Lastly, things will get better. It might take some work on your part, but you got through every day in your life so far. You can keep doing so, I have faith in you.
